
[1]refrigeratory

   REFRIG'ERATORY, a. Cooling; mitigating heat.

   REFRIG'ERATORY, n.

   1. In distillation, a vessel filled with cold water, through which the
   worm passes; by which means the vapors are condensed as they pass
   through the worm.

   2. Any thing internally cooling.
